results.name: Number of polyominoes without holes consisting of 7 regular unit n-gons.
link: Matthias Koch and Sascha Kurz, Enumeration of generalized polyominoes, arXiv:math.CO/0605144
example: a(3)=24 because there are 24 polyiamonds consisting of 7 triangles and a(4)=108 because there are 108 polyominoes consisting of 7 squares.
results.author: _Sascha Kurz_, Feb 07 2005
